Indeed, the act of teaching truly serves as the catalyst for deeper understanding. Your mention of the Protégé Effect resonates with the scientific underpinnings of active learning. For instance, research from the University of Washington supports the notion that teaching others significantly enhances one’s own comprehension, reinforcing the feedback loop you outlined.

